I think we all have experienced unexpected comparisons,

64
00:04:04,394 --> 00:04:06,694
like, you know, maybe like this or something else.

65
00:04:07,314 --> 00:04:09,955
But people will liken things that they hear to other things

66
00:04:09,995 --> 00:04:12,076
and that is often bewildering.

67
00:04:12,836 --> 00:04:14,656
And in this case, you know, genuinely,

68
00:04:14,676 --> 00:04:17,537
I have no idea what the hell is going on there.

69
00:04:17,877 --> 00:04:19,697
Maybe, again, the goal was, you know,

70
00:04:20,137 --> 00:04:25,179
sweeping and spiritual, and maybe to Nadine.

71
00:04:27,628 --> 00:04:29,710
Here's to you is sweeping and spiritual.

72
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:31,631
And so in that sense, maybe I succeeded.

73
00:04:31,671 --> 00:04:33,773
I have my doubts, but...

74
00:04:37,136 --> 00:04:40,699
So this was a recurring theme at some point.

75
00:04:42,141 --> 00:04:43,182
So relaxing.

76
00:04:43,682 --> 00:04:46,184
Austin Winery, the Brian Eno of soundtracks.

77
00:04:46,404 --> 00:04:47,125
I've got that too.

78
00:04:47,906 --> 00:04:48,366
It's weird.

79
00:04:49,247 --> 00:04:52,590
Again, I think we're hearing things differently.

80
00:04:53,682 --> 00:04:57,926
I really thought my goal explicitly was to be melodic, soaring, I'll say again.

81
00:04:58,567 --> 00:05:01,350
It turns out I'm actually being super meditative and tranquil.

82
00:05:02,531 --> 00:05:07,556
I have heard the word relaxing about my music so many times, and I don't think I've ever

83
00:05:07,777 --> 00:05:10,720
once tried to write something that was relaxing, except maybe Flo.

84
00:05:12,402 --> 00:05:13,062
Here's another one.

85
00:05:17,234 --> 00:05:24,058
Love me Jenny. Thank God I spotted one like that much later down the road

86
00:05:24,778 --> 00:05:28,841
because I think that's actually a compliment. I think they're actually

87
00:05:28,941 --> 00:05:33,243
trying to be nice and I'm hope that just as a defense mechanism I'm saying

88
00:05:33,263 --> 00:05:36,725
they're not sort of bored out of their mind but I don't know they fell asleep

89
00:05:36,745 --> 00:05:40,827
before they could type a question mark so it's hard to know for sure what we're

90
00:05:40,847 --> 00:05:41,288
even saying.

91
00:05:42,570 --> 00:05:48,111
Point is, Journey was repeatedly called out as relaxing, meditative, textural, things

92
00:05:48,151 --> 00:05:50,751
that I really didn't think was the goal.

93
00:05:51,111 --> 00:05:54,332
And the strange thing is, it wasn't people criticizing it.

94
00:05:54,532 --> 00:05:58,192
They were saying, this is what I like about it and identifying things that it explicitly

95
00:05:58,232 --> 00:05:58,892
was not trying to be.

96
00:06:01,073 --> 00:06:02,173
It gets weirder.

97
00:06:03,533 --> 00:06:05,694
I played this game after I got my wisdom teeth out.

98
00:06:06,274 --> 00:06:09,614
It relaxed me and took my mind away from the pain because I couldn't swallow the ibuprofen

99
00:06:09,634 --> 00:06:09,994
pills.

100
00:06:11,235 --> 00:06:11,775
So I'm like...

101
00:06:16,145 --> 00:06:20,548
I think the culmination was when IGN rated it the number one soundtrack for studying.

102
00:06:20,568 --> 00:06:28,274
Again, this is not something I can have any explanation.

103
00:06:28,394 --> 00:06:34,939
I would not have thought sweeping and soaring is compatible with studying, but this is where

104
00:06:35,859 --> 00:06:38,501
I was constantly learning this lesson over and over.

105
00:06:39,002 --> 00:06:41,844
So it might be something more like this.

106
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:46,244
I realize I can't predict what people are going to say or what their takeaway is going

107
00:06:46,264 --> 00:06:46,484
to be.

108
00:06:47,365 --> 00:06:50,929
And the bottom line is that's okay.

109
00:06:51,550 --> 00:06:52,751
It better be okay.

110
00:06:52,771 --> 00:06:58,718
We can't control it as much as we think we can or as much as we are specifically trying

111
00:06:58,758 --> 00:07:02,262
to evoke very precise images and feelings and things like that.

112
00:07:02,322 --> 00:07:03,444
We just can't.

113
00:07:04,491 --> 00:07:05,171
One more highlight.

114
00:07:06,573 --> 00:07:08,616
This is from a Journey YouTube upload.

115
