00:12:17,914 --> 00:12:19,555
and who we're working for has not got a clue,

206
00:12:19,955 --> 00:12:22,336
and they're just completely clueless and they don't know about music and all that.

207
00:12:22,356 --> 00:12:23,236
We know best and they're wrong.

208
00:12:23,876 --> 00:12:27,597
But I think that, like I've slowly realized over the years,

209
00:12:27,637 --> 00:12:29,038
that you can't think like that.

210
00:12:29,378 --> 00:12:31,559
Like, the minute you hire yourself out to somebody else,

211
00:12:32,099 --> 00:12:34,200
they're probably going to tell you what to do, and you probably better do it.

212
00:12:34,260 --> 00:12:36,961
Or you're probably going to get fired, and they're going to get Austin to do it instead.

213
00:12:37,461 --> 00:12:37,821
You know, so...

214
00:12:42,116 --> 00:12:45,658
So that's my thing about learning to let go of that ownership,

215
00:12:45,998 --> 00:12:48,040
that I think that you just have to be prepared

216
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:51,162
to be told that it's not what they want

217
00:12:51,382 --> 00:12:52,903
and you really should try to do it again.

218
00:12:53,443 --> 00:12:54,964
And no amount of arguing with them

219
00:12:54,984 --> 00:12:55,845
is going to make any difference.

220
00:12:56,205 --> 00:12:58,606
It's just going to go, I don't like it and that's it.

